#Correlation function for identifying correlated features over certain threshold and dropping 
# one of each pair of correlated features
def corr_func(x,threshold):
    corr_matrix = x.corr()
    iters = range(len(corr_matrix.columns) - 1)
    drop_cols = []
    print(iters)
    
    # Iterate through the correlation matrix and compare correlations
    for i in iters:
        for j in range(i+1):
            item = corr_matrix.iloc[j:(j+1), (i+1):(i+2)]
            col = item.columns
            row = item.index
            val = abs(item.values)
            # If correlation exceeds the threshold
            if val >= threshold:
                # Print the correlated features and the correlation value
                print(col.values[0], "|", row.values[0], "|", round(val[0][0], 2))
                drop_cols.append(col.values[0])
                print(drop_cols)
                # Drop one of each pair of correlated columns
    drops = set(drop_cols)
    x = x.drop(columns=drops,inplace=True)

    return x

In [119]:
 # Calculating VIF
from statsmodels.stats.outliers_influence import variance_inflation_factor
def calc_vif(X):
    # Calculating VIF
    vif = pd.DataFrame()
    vif["variables"] = X.columns
    vif["VIF"] = [variance_inflation_factor(X.values, i) for i in range(X.shape[1])]

    return(vif)

train_accuracy=[]
test_accuracy=[]
for train_index,test_index in kf.split(X):
    X_train,X_test=X.iloc[train_index],X.iloc[test_index]
    y_train,y_test=y.iloc[train_index],y.iloc[test_index]
    train_accuracy.append(accuracy_score(grid_cv.predict(X_train),y_train))
    test_accuracy.append(accuracy_score(grid_cv.predict(X_test),y_test))
print("Train Accuracy : {}".format(np.array(train_accuracy).mean()))
print("Test Accuracy  : {}".format(np.array(test_accuracy).mean()))
